Database : 
  Organized form, Re-use, Re-cover, Accessible, Large set of Data
2 Database :
 Relational(RDMS) = (structure: table, ACID, vertically scaling )
    Ex: MySQL, Oracle, PostgreSQL, Microsoft SQL Server, AWS Aurora

 Non - Relational(No Sql) = (No-structure: flexible, Horizontal scaling, BASE ) 
    Ex: MongoDB, Redis, DynamoDB
 

SQL - Structured Query Language

  To Relational db handle 
  (CRUD - CREATE, READ, UPDATE, DELETE)

MYSQL : TABLE (Rows-records, Columns-field)

Query - Basic commands

SELECT - Retrieve data
WHERE - Filter 
ORDER BY - Sort 
INSERT - Add
UPDATE - Modify
DELETE - Remove
CREATE - Create (db, table)
DROP - Delete (table)

SQL DATA TYPES

Numeric : INT (BIGINT SMALLINT TINYINT INT), DECIMAL, FLOAT,REAL, NUMERIC

Binary : BINARY, BLOB

String : CHAR, VARCHAR, TEXT

Boolean : BOOLEAN

Date/Time : DATE, TIME, DATETIME

Special : json, xml, aon ..


CREATE TABLE transc (
   TransID INT PRIMARY KEY,
   TransDATE DATE,
   TransTIME TIME
)
   
SQL OPERATORS

Arithmetic  + - / * %

Comparison = != <> <= >=

Logical AND OR NOT

Bitwise & | << >> ^ ~                 

Compound += -= *= /= %=


SET Salary = Salary + 3000;


CREATE - Database, table 

 USE ______ ;
 CREATE <TABLE NAME> ;

DROP - Deletes Tables

DROP <TABLE NAME> ;

ALTER - Column name

ALTER TABLE <> ADD mobileNumber int;
ALTER TABLE <> DROP city;
ALTER TABLE <> MODIFY COLUMN Address int;
ALTER TABLE <> RENAME COLUMN city TO country;

RENAME - To rename the database


INSERT INTO <table_name> (name , city, mobileNumber)  VALUES ('john', 'chennai', 289745419), ('john', 'chennai', 289745419), ('john', 'chennai', 289745419), ('john', 'chennai', 289745419);


TRUNCATE - Remove all records from the table not the table itself

