DATA CONSTRAINTS
-----------------

NOT NULL 
PRIMARY KEY - unique, not null
ALTERNATE Key -  unique, will allow null values, can have multiple <ak>
FOREGIN KEY - 

Student(name<fk>, id <pk>, mobilenumber<ak> , age , subjects, address<ak>, grade, class DEFAULT B, sec, mail UNIQUE) : Mark(name<fk>, mark) : Leave(name, noOFDays)

UNIQUE -  To give unique records for a column
   
CHECK - condition  CHECK( age >= 3 ) -- This will not give 
DEFAULT - To give default values for a specific column

TABLE : ALTER TABLE <>, COPY TABLE <>, RENAME TABLE <>, TEMP TABLE <>, TRUNCATE TABLE <>, DROP TABLE <>




